Good. I have everything I need. Your `signUp` call at [Auth.tsx:173-182](src/pages/Auth.tsx#L173-L182) is already correct — `emailRedirectTo` is set to `${window.location.origin}/auth` which is exactly right. Here is the complete execution guide.

---

## Requirement 1 — Supabase Dashboard SMTP Configuration

### Step 1: Get your Resend SMTP credentials

1. Log in to [resend.com](https://resend.com) → **API Keys** → Create a new key with **Full Access** (or at minimum **Sending Access**).
2. Copy the key — it looks like `re_xxxxxxxxxx`. You will not see it again.
3. Verify your sending domain under **Domains** (e.g. `crevia.app` or `mail.crevia.app`). Add the DNS records Resend gives you (SPF, DKIM, DMARC) to your domain registrar. **Do not skip this** — unverified domains get rejected in production.

### Step 2: Configure SMTP in Supabase

Navigate to: **Supabase Dashboard → Project → Authentication → Settings → SMTP Settings**

Toggle **"Enable Custom SMTP"** ON, then fill in:

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Sender name** | `Crevia` |
| **Sender email** | `noreply@yourdomain.com` *(must match your verified Resend domain)* |
| **Host** | `smtp.resend.com` |
| **Port** | `465` |
| **Minimum interval** | `60` *(seconds between emails per user — keep at default or lower to 30)* |
| **Username** | `resend` *(literal string "resend", not your email)* |
| **Password** | `re_xxxxxxxxxx` *(your Resend API key from Step 1)* |

> **Port note:** Use `465` (SSL/TLS). Resend also supports `587` (STARTTLS) and `2465`, but `465` is the most reliable for Supabase's mailer.

### Step 3: Verify

Supabase has a **"Send test email"** button at the bottom of the SMTP settings panel. Use it. If it lands in inbox (not spam), the pipe is working. If it fails, the error message will tell you exactly why (wrong key, unverified domain, etc.).

---

## Requirement 2 — Email Template

Navigate to: **Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → Email Templates → Confirm signup**

Paste this into the **Body** field. Set **Subject** to: `Confirm your Crevia account`

```html
