```

**Critical:** The `{{ .ConfirmationURL }}` variable is Supabase's Go template syntax. Do not modify it. Supabase injects the full signed URL at send time, including the `token_hash` and `type=signup` params — your existing `onAuthStateChange` listener handles it automatically.

---

## Requirement 3 — React Frontend

**Zero changes required.** This is a pure backend infrastructure swap. Here is why each part of your existing code remains correct:

| Your code | Status | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `emailRedirectTo: ${window.location.origin}/auth` ([Auth.tsx:177](src/pages/Auth.tsx#L177)) | Correct | Resend delivers the email; Supabase still controls the confirmation URL. The redirect target doesn't change. |
| `emailConfirmPending` state ([Auth.tsx:36](src/pages/Auth.tsx#L36)) | Correct | Your "Check your inbox" screen already handles the `signUpData.session === null` case at [Auth.tsx:216](src/pages/Auth.tsx#L216). |
| `onAuthStateChange` listener ([Auth.tsx:70](src/pages/Auth.tsx#L70)) | Correct | Handles `SIGNED_IN` after the user clicks the email link and lands back on `/auth` with `token_hash`. |
| `hasOAuthCallback()` guard ([Auth.tsx:14](src/pages/Auth.tsx#L14)) | Correct | Checks for `token_hash` in the URL params, which Supabase appends to the `emailRedirectTo` URL — works identically. |

---

## Production Checklist Before Going Live

1. DNS records for your Resend domain are fully propagated (check with `dig TXT yourdomain.com`)
2. Resend "Send test email" from the Supabase SMTP panel lands in inbox, not spam
3. Do an end-to-end test: sign up with a real email → confirm receipt → click link → land on `/auth` → `onAuthStateChange` fires `SIGNED_IN` → redirect to `/kira`
4. Set Supabase **Auth → Settings → "Confirm email"** to **Enabled** if it isn't already — otherwise no confirmation email is sent regardless of SMTP config

